<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id771bd45d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s231d"><num value="231d">§ 231d.</num><heading> Repeal of inconsistent laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">All Acts or parts of Acts inconsistent with this subchapter are repealed to the extent of such inconsistency.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id771bd45e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1939-08-10/ch640/s5">Aug. 10, 1939, ch. 640, § 5</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/53/1342">53 Stat. 1342</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
